[{"headline":"Basic Overview Of React js","image":"https://github.com/skptricks/reacthostinghome/blob/image/11.jpg?raw=true","editor":"Sumit Kumar Pradhan","keywords":"Basic Overview Of React js","wordcount":8752,"publisher":"React Beginners","url":"https://www.reactbeginners.com/post/basic-overview-of-react-js/","datePublished":"September 1, 2019","dateModified":"2019-09-01T14:44:26.420Z","tag":["React"," Javascript"," Web Development"],"location":"US","articleBody":"<p>Today we have started new series for programming language that is Reactjs and here we will cover all topic related to react.&nbsp;React is a front-end library developed by Facebook. It is currently one of the most popular JavaScript libraries and has a strong foundation and large community behind it. It is used for handling the view layer for web and mobile apps. ReactJS allows us to create reusable UI components.&nbsp;React JS is specifically designed in such a way that it has a mid interactive layer called Virtual DOM which in turn interacts with DOM. This Virtual DOM helps in data loading very faster.<br style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"><br style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"></p><div class=\"separator\" style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; clear: both; text-align: center; cursor: auto;\"><img width=\"476\" height=\"246\" alt=\"11.jpg\" src=\"https://github.com/skptricks/reacthostinghome/blob/image/11.jpg?raw=true\" style=\"min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px;\" class=\"e-rte-image e-imgcenter e-resize\"></div><p><br style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"><a name=\"more\" style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(60, 192, 145); font-weight: 700;\"></a><br style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"></p><h2 style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; position: relative; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(44, 62, 80);\"><b style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: orange;\">Who is the target audience?</span></b></h2><ul style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0.5em 0px; padding: 0px 2.5em 0px 15px; line-height: 1.5;\"><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Programmers looking to learn React</li><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Developers who want to grow out of just using jQuery</li><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Engineers who have researched React but have had trouble mastering some concepts.</li></ul><div style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><br style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"></div><h2 style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; position: relative; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(44, 62, 80);\"><b style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: orange;\">Benefits&nbsp;of Reactjs:</span></b></h2><div style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><ul style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0.5em 0px; padding: 0px 2.5em 0px 15px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; letter-spacing: normal;\"><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Single Page Application.</li><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Entire page remains same but only few components change.</li><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Code is easy to scale and maintain.</li><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">More functionalities as HTML is created from JS.</li><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Isomorphic Rendering(Server side rendering).</li><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Blazing speed because all the rendering part controlled by states rather DOM.</li></ul><div style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; letter-spacing: normal;\"><br style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"></div><div style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; letter-spacing: normal;\"><h2 style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; position: relative; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(44, 62, 80);\"><b style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s;\"><span style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: orange;\">What Will You Learn?</span></b></h2><div style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><ul style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0.5em 0px; padding: 0px 2.5em 0px 15px; line-height: 1.5;\"><li style=\"outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; line-height: 1.5;\">Build amazing sing